GAUTENG police have issued a reward of R100 000 to anyone who can come forth with information that can lead to the arrest of suspect Mbuso Ndabazovela Biyela. The suspect is wanted for multiple cases of murder that occurred between 2017 and this year in Jabulani and Lenasia, Gauteng as well as in Nquthu, KZN. “The suspect is tall, light in complexion and deemed armed and very dangerous. Anyone with information that can lead to the arrest of the suspect as well as the conviction is urged to call Major-General Mbuso Khumalo on 082 555 8642, and Colonel Friccah Masilela on 082 822 7270,” Colonel Dimakatso Sello said in a statement. She said the public can also call CrimeStop on 08600 10111 if they have information. “Tip-offs can also be submitted via the My SAPS app. All received information will be treated as confidential.”